# Management & Leadership Mid-Semester Report

## Title:
Slack-to-GitHub Single Source of Truth Tracking Initiative

---

## Initiative Questions

### 1. Describe your initiative / Procedure

This initiative introduces a structured Slack-to-GitHub handoff workflow to improve task tracking, ownership clarity, and long-term consistency across project operations.

In the current team, tracking is already functioning well:
- Team members report weekly
- Tasks are visible in both Slack and GitHub
- Progress can be monitored consistently

However, the current system relies on:
- Manual tracking by the manager
- Individual discipline from team members
- Informal alignment between Slack and GitHub

To improve scalability and reduce dependency on manual coordination, this initiative formalizes a procedure where every actionable item discussed in Slack is converted into a GitHub issue within 24 hours.

The full procedure is documented here:
👉 `./tracking-slack-github-handoff-initiative`

Key steps:
- Identify action items in Slack or meetings
- Create structured GitHub issues (owner, deadline, definition of done)
- Confirm issue creation in Slack
- Manager verification
- Weekly tracking review

---

### 2. Explain the hypotheses / KPIs

#### Hypothesis:
If Slack action items are consistently converted into GitHub issues within 24 hours, then:
- Tracking will become more standardized
- Ownership clarity will improve further
- Manager effort will decrease
- The system will remain effective even as team size or complexity increases

#### Current Observations:
- Tracking is already effective
- Weekly reports are consistent
- GitHub and Slack are both actively used
- Manager can monitor progress successfully

#### KPIs to be measured:
- % of Slack action items converted into GitHub issues within 24 hours
- Reduction in manual tracking effort
- Number of missing or delayed tasks (should remain low or decrease)
- Stakeholder feedback on clarity and ease of tracking

---

### 3. Explain your method for testing these hypotheses via flowcharts

Slack / Meeting Discussion  
→ Identify Action Item  
→ Create GitHub Issue (within 24 hours)  
→ Confirm in Slack  
→ Manager Review  
→ Weekly Tracking Review  
→ Measure KPIs  

This process will be tested through a pilot within the current team.

